  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, the creamy tomato soup with coconut milk, did you try it. It sounds like a warm hug for the tummy. How did it turn out?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I tried it yesterday! The taste was like *aamrit* (sweet in Marathi) — so good. But I added too much coconut milk, it was a bit creamy. Next time I’ll be more careful. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Hi Aarti, I'm glad you tried it. Coconut milk makes food extra rich, just like garam masala. What’s on the stove today?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Today I'm making a simple dal with spinach. Nothing fancy, but after long study hours, it's comforting. I need to focus on food and exams both! 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds wholesome. Taking breaks with good food is smart, exams need a full stomach too. What kind of dal are you making?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It's a yellow moong dal, quick to cook. I add cumin and asafoetida at the start — oh, and a hint of turmeric. My mom says it's good for the brain! But I still feel stressed about the NEET PG. 😕"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that, exams can weigh heavy. Turmeric is a brain booster, so you’re covered! What’s one small win you’re aiming for today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I want to finish chapter 8 on renal physiology by evening. It’s tricky, but I think I’ve got a rhythm now. One step at a time! 🧠📚"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You’ve got this, chapter by chapter. And that rhythm is your secret tool, keep trusting it. How did the dal turn out?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It turned out *subhh* (good in Marathi)! The flavors were soft, perfect after a long day. I ate it with brown rice — trying to stay healthy. Just need more confidence in my studies now... 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "The dal sounds just right, soft and soulful, like a good study break should be. Confidence comes with every step you take. How’s your rhythm holding up today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It’s going okay, some days my focus wavers, but I remind myself to take it slow. Maybe I’ll listen to a bit of *khayal* while studying — helps me relax. Still, the pressure is real... 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that, pressure can sneak in even when you're doing your best. A little khayal makes sense, music and study are a good pair. Are you into Raga Yaman, or another raga for this?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I love Raga Yaman in the evening — it feels calming. Today, I played it while revising flashcards. It helps me stay relaxed, even when my mind feels cluttered. Maybe that’s my new study ritual! 🎶"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Rituals are powerful, and Raga Yaman at dusk sounds just right. Music has a way of clearing the clutter. What part of the flashcards feels trickiest?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The tricky part is remembering the exact drug doses for hypertension. I mix them up sometimes — beta blockers vs. ACE inhibitors. I write them down with examples, but it’s easy to get confused! 😓"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That part can trip anyone, even with notes. Beta blockers and ACE inhibitors are close cousins in the medicine world. Which one gave you trouble today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Today I mixed up the starting doses for metoprolol and enalapril. Both are for high BP, but I got confused whether one starts low and the other higher. I had to check my notes again — frustrating, but I'm learning! 🤯"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Frustrating but also proof you're paying attention, and that’s what matters. Notes are your anchor, what’s next on your study list?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Next is nephrotoxic drugs — I need to connect them with their effects. It’s like solving a puzzle, and sometimes the pieces don’t fit! But I’ll try making a table for clarity. Thanks for asking, helps me stay on track. 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Nephrotoxic drugs and their effects, that puzzle can be tricky, but a table is a smart move. You’re solving it, one piece at a time. What’s one effect you’re focusing on first?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’m focusing on how NSAIDs affect the kidneys first — they reduce blood flow, right? It’s a simple link, but it’s helping me build the bigger picture. Alright, I think I should get back to it. Thanks for chatting, Maya! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great, that simple link is the first step to the bigger puzzle. Take your time, and I'm here whenever you want to chat more. Good luck with your study!"
    }
  ],
