      },
      {
        "id": "mo_005",
        "text": "I feel guilty about cooking instead of studying, even though it helps me feel productive—but I feel like I'm slacking",
        "tone": "anxious",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-02",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-02",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_006",
        "text": "I just feel so stuck today; my brain feels like it's underwater",
        "tone": "frustrated",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-02",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-02",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_007",
        "text": "I'm worried I'll get practice questions wrong and lose motivation completely",
        "tone": "scared",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-02",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-02",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_008",
        "text": "Finding myself in The Namesake—the main character's struggle between two cultures mirrors my own experience of growing up Marathi at home but learning everything in English. It's what makes stories so relatable.",
        "tone": "content",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-05",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-05",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_009",
        "text": "I want to write fiction after exams—it feels like the creative outlet I'm putting on hold for now.",
        "tone": "hopeful",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-05",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-05",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_010",
        "text": "I have no real study plan. I just read the first paragraph, get bored, then panic. It's the same pattern every time.",
        "tone": "anxious",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-07",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-07",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_011",
        "text": "During practice tests, my mind goes blank and I feel so sad, like all my effort isn't helping.",
        "tone": "sad",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_012",
        "text": "I don't know why I find it so hard. Maybe I'm just not cut out for this.",
        "tone": "scared",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-10",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-10",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_013",
        "text": "Everyone laughed when I mixed up the drug dosages, but I just wanted to disappear. It's so embarrassing.",
        "tone": "scared",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-11",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-11",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_014",
        "text": "I just sat in my room hugging my dog. He doesn't judge me, at least.",
        "tone": "grateful",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-11",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-11",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_015",
        "text": "I created a new mantra: 'Even dogs make mistakes, but they keep wagging their tails.' It helps me laugh at myself.",
        "tone": "hopeful",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-11",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-11",
        "mentions": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "mo_016",
        "text": "The mock test went better than expected. I didn't mix up any dosages and finished early. The dog mantra worked.",
        "tone": "proud",
        "sensitive": false,
        "first_seen": "2026-05-11",
        "last_seen": "2026-05-11",
        "mentions": 1
      },
